Instructional video used a different (older) version of Canva, so I was unable to follow exactly what the instructor was doing.  I could not link pages from the main menu to the rest of the website.  So in the end I had five pages which could be scrolled up and down like a power point, but could not jump from the top or to other sites or pages.  I think if I paid more money it might be better, but this was a work project so I didn't have to pay.  Because of the difficulty I am not sure if I would pay to use it in the future.  If a need arose I might, but from my experience I am not sure I would depend on it for an important project.  I would need more time to play with it to figure it out.
